text: I've got brews on the mind today... should I be building Squee or Atogatog?
I’m interested in hearing about both. Pitch each one in two sentences!

[[Squee, Goblin Nabob]] comes back from your graveyard to your hand each upkeep. While many an EDH player have lamented the fact that playing him as commander doesn't allow you to put together the old Squee-[[Survival of the Fittest]] combo from the days of yore, I for one would point out that in recent years "rummaging" aka "red loot" has become a thing which could be a lot of fun to pursue.

text: Atogatog is an atog that eats atogs. Typically you would play him with atogs.

I think Squee sounds fun, but I don’t know if using Squee to just pitch to rummages in a Good basis for a deck, even though that can be an incredible amount of value. How would you win?

Atogatog sounds like it could have some pretty fun graveyard and dying interaction since you have access to all 5 colors. My first thought is Grave Pact and Dictate of Erebos :stuck_out_tongue_closed_eyes:
I dunno, I've always been a value engine first, figure out how to win later kind of builder.
For sure you'll have a graveyard full of stuff besides Squee by the end, so flashback and stuff like [[Magnivore]] is an option.

text:
When I usually build my decks I figure out my draw and ramp first, and then throw in my wincons, that way I’m always able to play Magic, and never just spinning my wheels. 

That being said, Atogatog sounds better, but using Squee for value sounds much more fun if we can make sure that we aren’t just drawing cards. [[Conflagrate]] could be a potential include if you’re able to keep your hand full.
